<P>
CSUN MEN SWEEP IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Samuelson recorded 7 kills and Raphael Tulino had 6 as Cal State Northridge 
rolled to a 15-12, 15-0, 15-4 victory over Chapman in a men's volleyball match 
Thursday at Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors started slowly, committing 8 hitting errors in the first game. 
</P>
<P>
But in the final 2 games Northridge hit at a .333 pace while limiting Chapman 
to a minus-.028 kill percentage. 
</P>
<P>
The Matadors travel to UC San Diego on Saturday for their final nonconference 
match. 
</P>
