<P>
Sun Microsystems Inc. said net income for the second quarter more than doubled 
to $29.5 million. Revenue rose 91% to $448.3 million. The Mountain View, 
Calif., high-tech firm said the shortage of memory chips, crucial to Sun's 
high-performance workstations and servers, abated somewhat toward the end of 
the quarter. "Yet, despite the increase in production and shipments resulting 
from improved component availability, the high rate of incoming orders in the 
second quarter again resulted in the largest quarter-end backlog in Sun's 
