<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Caterpillar Inc.'s earnings slipped 4% in the fourth quarter to $163 million 
despite better sales, but it still managed to earn a record profit for the full 
year. Even with the dip in quarterly profit, Caterpillar said 1988 profit was a 
record $616 million, up from $350 million in 1987. The Peoria, Ill.-based 
heavy-machinery manufacturer said higher costs in the fourth quarter came from 
a new labor contract, higher employment, factory modernization investment and 
more expensive materials. During the final quarter, revenue rose 17% to $2.66 
billion. For the year, Caterpillar said annual sales rose to $10.43 billion 
from $8.18 billion in 1987. 
</P>
