<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOME TECH: VIDEO NEWS; 
</P>
<P>
REVIEW; 
</P>
<P>
****EXCELLENT ***GOOD **ORDINARY *POOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
****"The International Tournee of Animation, Volume I: The 19th Tournee." 
Expanded Entertainment, $39. 
</P>
<P>
This collection of 14 excellent shorts from nine countries showcases the 
diversity of world animation. Dujan Petricic's outrageous re-telling of "Romeo 
and Juliet" (Yugoslavia) with monsters, and "Charade" (Canada), John Minnis' 
Oscar-winning parody of parlor games, recapture the hilarity of the classic 
Hollywood cartoons. A second Academy Award-winner, Borge Ring's "Anna and 
Bella" (Holland), in which two aged sisters reminisce about their shared lives, 
shows how a talented artist can capture the most deeply felt emotions in a few 
simple lines. An exceptional package of films. Information: (213) 473-6701. 
CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
