<P>
PACIFIC 10 ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CAL KNOCKS OFF 20TH-RANKED STANFORD, 75-64 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leonard Taylor had 21 points and 12 rebounds, leading California to a 75-64 
Pacific 10 Conference upset of 20th-ranked Stanford Thursday night at Berkeley. 
</P>
<P>
Cal (13-5 overall, 4-3 in the Pac-10) scored 14 consecutive points and held 
Stanford scoreless during 5 1/2 minutes late in game to take command. The Bears 
hit 24 of 29 free throws in the second half, including 16 in a row at one 
point. 
</P>
<P>
Todd Lichti scored 18 points for Stanford (13-4, 5-2). 
</P>
<P>
Oregon State 71, Washington 70 -- Gary Payton scored 14 of his 19 points in the 
second half, and the Beavers rallied from a 13-point deficit to beat the 
Huskies at Corvallis, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
The Beavers (11-4, 4-3) scored 11 straight points to take a 70-61 lead with 
1:46 left and held on despite making only 1 of 5 free throws down the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
Eldridge Recasner scored 23 points for Washington (5-9, 2-5). 
</P>
<P>
Oregon 67, Washington State 49 -- Frank Johnson scored 18 of his 22 points in 
the second half as the Ducks downed the Cougars at Eugene, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing, 24-23, at halftime, Oregon (7-8, 2-3) took control with a 21-6 surge 
in the first 9 minutes of the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Harold Wright scored 11 points for Washington State (6-9, 1-5). 
</P>
