</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOYOLA PLAYS GONZAGA AT SPOKANE TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN DROOZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Loyola Marymount will play the Northwest portion of its West Coast Athletic 
Conference basketball schedule with games against Gonzaga at Spokane, Wash., 
tonight and at Portland Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
The Lions (8-6) are tied for first in the WCAC with St. Mary's and Pepperdine 
at 2-0. Gonzaga (10-5) and Portland (1-14) are both 1-1 in the conference. 
</P>
<P>
Loyola continues to lead the nation in scoring with an average of 113 points a 
game, behind its high-scoring trio of Hank Gathers, 33.9 points; Jeff Fryer, 
23.8, and Enoch Simmons, 20.6. 
</P>
<P>
Gonzaga is 5-1 at home but has a thin lineup without center Paul Verret, who 
broke an ankle recently. Guards Doug Spradley and Jim McPhee carry the load, 
combining for an average of 40 points a game. ALAN DROOZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
