<HEADLINE>
<P>
STAYING ON TOP OF THE SHAKE-UP; 
</P>
<P>
MOTHER NATURE'S RUMBLINGS PUNCTUATE SOUTHLAND SHOWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The whole lotta shakin' did little to interfere with the whole lotta shakin' on 
the local rock concert scene. In West Hollywood, Curt Kirkwood of the 
Phoenix-based Meat Puppets was resting in the Roxy dressing room between the 
band's two shows Wednesday and hardly noticed the temblor. 
</P>
<P>
"(Opening band) Pygmy Love Circus had just done its sound check," Kirkwood said 
Thursday. "Then someone said, 'Did you feel that?' I said I just thought it was 
the kick drum. . . . I always think I feel earthquakes (in Los Angeles) 
though." 
</P>
<P>
But Wally Ross, publicist for the band's label, SST Records, had a different 
suggestion: "It was the Meat Puppets that caused the earthquake." 
</P>
