<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UNIVERSITY ACCEPTS CHARITY, STAYS UNBEATEN IN LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY NISTA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
University High School broke open a close game in the third quarter and coasted 
to a 56-38 victory over foul-prone Newport Harbor in a Sea View League girls' 
basketball game Thursday at University. 
</P>
<P>
The Trojans (15-4 overall, 4-0 in league play) made 24 of 39 free throws; 
Newport Harbor hit 3 of 7 from the line. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor (3-13, 1-3) had 4 players foul out in the fourth quarter after 
the Trojans had built a commanding lead. 
</P>
<P>
Shelley Davis and Denise Gandara each scored 18 points for University. 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor trailed, 22-16, at halftime and scored the first 4 points in the 
third quarter to trail by 2 points. 
</P>
<P>
But University went on a 12-2 run, including a technical foul on Newport Harbor 
Coach David Barela. 
</P>
<P>
"We rebounded a lot better in the second half," University Coach Doug Sorey 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, who scored 5 of her 18 points on free throws, grabbed 12 rebounds. 
Stacey Giem led Newport Harbor with 17 points before fouling out. 
</P>
<P>
"We went to the trap and that stopped Giem from getting off her shot," Sorey 
said. 
</P>
<P>
University scored the first 12 points of the game and took a 13-4 lead by the 
end of the first quarter. LARRY NISTA 
</P>
</TEXT>
