<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
GORBACHEV CONGRATULATES BUSH, HOPES FOR STABLE U.S. RELATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet leader Mikhail S. Gorbachev congratulated President Bush on his 
inauguration today and expressed hope that superpower relations will be stable 
during his term in office, Tass press agency said. 
</P>
<P>
In his message to the new President, Gorbachev said Bush is coming to power in 
an atmosphere of improved Soviet-American ties. "Further joint efforts by the 
Soviet Union and the United States will make it possible substantially to bring 
closer the solution of the most painful problems of the present time, above all 
those connected with the need to eliminate the threat of war," Gorbachev said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
