<P>
SAKHAROV, REJECTED BY ACADEMY, NOMINATED FOR SEAT IN PARLIAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Human rights activist Andrei D. Sakharov was nominated as a parliamentary 
candidate for a Moscow district today amid an outcry over his surprise 
rejection by the leadership of the Academy of Sciences two days before. 
</P>
<P>
Workers at Moscow's Lebedev Physics Institute nominated the physicist and Nobel 
Peace laureate for the Oktyabrskaya district of the Soviet capital by more than 
1,500 votes in favor and 22 against, according to people who attended a meeting 
there. The Academy's Presidium on Wednesday rejected Sakharov and more than 100 
other candidates without first consulting ordinary members. (Story, Page 16.) 
