<P>
EGYPTIAN POLICE STATION ATTACKED; EXTREMIST KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAIRO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Egyptian police were looking for about 30 Muslim militants Thursday after an 
attack on a police station in which one man was killed, security sources said. 
</P>
<P>
They said a group of fundamentalists, apparently seeking weapons, attacked a 
police station on Tuesday at El Minya, 150 miles south of Cairo. 
</P>
<P>
Sobhi Yehia Saad, a 27-year-old member of the banned Jihad organization, was 
killed when security forces moved in to stop the attackers from ransacking the 
police post in an apartment block next to a mosque where the militants have set 
up their stronghold. 
</P>
<P>
The fundamentalists regard most music, television shows and dancing as 
blasphemous and are seeking to enforce strict Islamic laws in several 
districts. 
</P>
