<P>
BANGLADESH COLD KILLS 70 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DHAKA, Bangladesh 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The coldest weather in Bangladesh in 20 years has killed at least 70 people in 
the past week, police said Thursday. They said most of the victims were 
villagers who slept outside or in straw and mud huts after recent floods and 
cyclones destroyed their homes. Overnight lows have been around 40 degrees, and 
icy winds have added to people's misery. 
</P>
