<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON LANDS PASADENA PLAYER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Washington Huskies landed one football player, but lost another. 
</P>
<P>
Charles Mincey, a cornerback from Pasadena City College, has told the Huskies 
he plans to sign a letter of intent Feb. 8 to play football for Washington. 
</P>
<P>
But Glen Cavanaugh, a 6-foot-4, 265-pound lineman from Gonzaga Prep High School 
in Spokane, said he will attend Stanford University, the Seattle 
Post-Intelligencer reported today. Washington and Washington State both 
recruited Cavanaugh. 
</P>
<P>
Mincey, who prepped at Los Angeles' Dorsey High School, also was recruited by 
UCLA, USC, Pittsburgh and Iowa State. 
</P>
<P>
The Huskies rarely recruit junior college football players. They've signed only 
six transfers, three of them kickers, in the last seven seasons. 
</P>
</TEXT>
